AB  - This paper develops a ‘monetary’ approach for the analysis of tariff policy under a free (flexible) exchange rate regime. The paper concludes that the imposition of a tariff unambiguously causes a deterioration in the level of employment under free rates even without a Laursen-Metzler effect on saving.
