T1  - The terms-of-trade effect on expenditure: Some evidence from econometric models
AU  - Deardorff, Alan V.
AU  - Stern, Robert M.
JO  - Journal of International Economics
VL  - 8
IS  - 3
SP  - 409
EP  - 414
PY  - 1978
DA  - 1978/08/01/
SN  - 0022-1996
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0022-1996(78)90004-1
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0022199678900041
AB  - The terms-of-trade effect on expenditure has been a long-recognized theoretical construct. In this paper, we examine the empirical credibility of this effect, using the expenditure equations of several large econometric models in terms of their formulation of real versus nominal variables. We find evidence of both positive and negative effects of import prices on various categories of expenditure. Thus, there is no consensus as to the direction of the terms-of-trade effect.
